      "writtenOn": "2021-06-04T14:51:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When we start supporting image filter DAGs, the native SkImageFilters can end up being shared (referenced from other SkImageFilters plus the native instance stored in Java).  In that case, the Java wrapper is not the exclusive owner and cannot straight delete. We need to unref instead and let the ref-counting machinery handle deletion: \n\n  SkSafeUnref(reinterpret_cast\u003c\u003e(...));",
      "range": {
